==Overview== The Kinzaki Kofun cluster is located behind [[Shimane University]], on a small hill overlooking the lowlands downstream of the Asakumi River to the south. It consists of two "two conjoined rectangles" type ({{ill|''{{ill|zenpō-kōhō-fun|comment=doing this because of the mass replacement error that gets rid of the links like this otherwise|lt=zenpō-kōhō-fun|ja|前方後方墳|lt=Zenpō-kōhō-fun|1=Zenpō-kōhō-fun|comment=doing this because I need to differentiate it in piped links too with my new interwiki tool as not the ambiguous phrase keyhole shaped kofun|1=zenpō-kōhō-fun|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/zenpō-kōhō-fun|13=User:Immanuelle/zenpō-kōhō-fun|qq=}}''|前方後方墳|lt=Zenpō-kōhō-fun|1=Zenpō-kōhō-fun|comment=doing this because I need to differentiate it in piped links too with my new interwiki tool as not the ambiguous phrase keyhole shaped kofun|1=zenpō-kōhō-fun}}), and three {{ill|Square Kofun|lt=square-type|ja|方墳|1=Square Kofun|1=Square Kofun|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Square Kofun|13=User:Immanuelle/Square Kofun|qq=}} ({{nihongo|''hōfun''|方墳|1=Square Kofun|1=Square Kofun}}) ''kofun''. There were originally 11 Kofuns, but six were destroyed due to the construction of a nearby housing complex in 1963. [[Archaeological excavation]] of Kofun No. 1 in 1947 determined that the [[burial chamber]] was a pit-style stone chamber made of split stones. A wide variety of [[grave goods]] were excavated, including a [[bronze mirror]] with a flower pattern, several ''[[magatama]]'' and several other types of beads, an iron blade, and [[Sue pottery]] pottery. The Sue pottery belongs to the oldest style in the San'in region, and there are few unusual examples such as vessel stands, vessels with bells, and vessels with legs.<ref name="Shiseki">{{cite book |last1=Isomura |first1=Yukio |last2=Sakai |first2=Hideya |title=(国指定史跡事典) National Historic Site Encyclopedia |date=2012 |publisher=学生社 |isbn=4311750404}}{{in lang|ja}}</ref>
The site is approximately 3.4 kilometers, or a 40-minute walk, north of [[Matsue Station]] on the [[JR West]] [[San'in Main Line]].
{| class="wikitable" style="text-align:center;background:#ffffff;white-space:nowrap;font-size:85%" |+ Kinzaki Kofun cluster !name !type !Size |- | Kinzaki No.1||''zenpō-kōhō-fun''||total length 32 meters: anterior: 12 x 14 x 1 meters; posterior 20 x 23.5 x 3 meters |- | Kinzaki No. 2|| ''hōfun'' || 10 x 10 x 1 meters |- | Kinzaki No. 3|| ''hōfun'' || 20 x 20 x 2 meters |- | Kinzaki No. 4|| ''hōfun'' || 26.5 x 17 x 3 meters |- | Kinzaki No.5||''zenpō-kōhō-fun''||total length 22 meters: anterior: 5 x 7.5 x 1 meters; posterior 17 x 20 x 2.5 meters |}
