The {{nihongo|'''Kinzaki Kofun cluster'''|金崎古墳群| Kinzaki Kofun-gun}} is a group of [[Kofun period]] [[kofun|Kofun]]s located in Nishikawatsu neighborhood of the city of {{ill|Matsue|en|Matsue|qid=Q207321|lt=Matsue|1=Matsue}}, {{ill|Shimane Prefecture|en|Shimane Prefecture|qid=Q132751|lt=Shimane Prefecture|1=Shimane Prefecture}}, in the {{ill|San&#39;in region|en|San&#39;in region|qid=Q398310|lt=San&#39;in region|1=San'in region}} of {{ill|Japan|en|Japan|qid=Q17|lt=Japan|1=Japan}}. The tumuli were collectively designated a National Historic Site in 1957.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://bunka.nii.ac.jp/heritages/detail/139367|title=金崎古墳群|trans-title= Kinzaki Kofun-gun|language=Japanese |publisher=[[Agency for Cultural Affairs]] |accessdate=August 31, 2022}}</ref>
